com.ignoubadhega.studycentremanager.dao

Interface GenericDao<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the Entity

    public interface GenericDao<E>
    Represent a contract for a Generic DAO(Data Access Object) Implementation.

    Some Definitions:

    Entity: The POJO object representing a Database table.
    Parameter: The Wrapper object representing the individual Attribute of a Entity or in Database point of view it's an abstraction for the Column of a Database Table.

    Author:
    praveen

      • findEntitiesHavingAllParams

        java.util.Collection<E> findEntitiesHavingAllParams(java.util.Collection<com.ignoubadhega.studycentremanager.dao.Parameter<?>> param,
                                                    java.lang.Class<E> entityClass)
        Finds and returns Collection of all the matching Domain Entities By using params as a query parameters and criteria for matching is based upon: every param inside param will be matched against the parameters in Entity.
        returns an empty Collection if no assosciated Entity is found.

        Note: Any Entity in the the returned collection will have all the parameters as in param. Through database point of view this is same as fetching all the rows in a table by using AND Operator on multiple column names in a where clause.

        Parameters:
        param - The query Parameter.
        entityClass - The Java type of the Entity.
        Returns:
        Entities having all the parameters as in param.

      • findEntitiesHavingAnyParams

        java.util.Collection<E> findEntitiesHavingAnyParams(java.util.Collection<com.ignoubadhega.studycentremanager.dao.Parameter<?>> param,
                                                    java.lang.Class<E> entityClass)
        Finds and returns Collection of all the matching Domain Entities By using params as a query parameters and criteria for matching is based upon: Any param inside param will be matched against the parameters in Entity i.e. if the Entity that is being processed has any of the parameters in Param as a parameter then it will pass the match.
        returns an empty Collection if no assosciated Entity is found.

        Note: Any Entity in the the returned collection will have atleast one of the parameters as in param. Through database point of view this is semantically same as fetching all the rows in a table by using OR Operator on multiple column names in a where clause.

        Parameters:
        param - The query Parameter.
        entityClass - The Java type of the Entity.
        Returns:
        Entities having all the parameters as in param.

      • findAllEntityParamVals

        <A> java.util.Collection<A> findAllEntityParamVals(com.ignoubadhega.studycentremanager.dao.Parameter<A> param,
                                                   java.lang.Class<E> entityClass)
        finds and returns all the parameter values of any single parameter type having the type and name information encapsulated in param for an Entity of java type entityClass.

        In a database point of view this is semantically same as finding all the values in any single column for any table.

        Type Parameters:
        A - the type of the parameter value.
        Parameters:
        param - the parameter object encapsulating the parameter type and name information.
        entityClass - the java type of Entity.
        Returns:
        collection of all the parameter values.
